    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Description\n\nHi,\n\nI ran into a problem with rst file and ltex_plus.\n\nltex_plus would not run, although the buffer is correctly attached to the LSP client. The log says: \n\n```\n[ERROR][2026-05-13 17:14:50] ...nvim-linux-x86_64/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/log.lua:151\t\"rpc\"\t\"ltex-ls-plus\"\t\"stderr\"\t\"mai 13, 2026 5:14:50 PM org.bsplines.ltexls.server.DocumentChecker checkAnnotatedTextFragment\\nPRÉCIS: Skipping text check as LTeX has been disabled for files with code language ID 'restructuredtext' via ltex.enabled\\n\"\n```\n\nIn the current `lsp/ltex_plus.lua` config file we can see that [`rst` is in the `filetype` config table](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/master/lsp/ltex_plus.lua#L53), and in the [`settings.ltex.enabled` table](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/master/lsp/ltex_plus.lua#L80) as well.\n\nI had the idea to remove [this line in `language_id_mapping` function](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/master/lsp/ltex_plus.lua#L30), which maps `rst` to `restructuredtext`, and it resolved my issue, but I want to be sure that it's the right thing to do, and that it has no side effect.\n\nThanks, regards.\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-13T19:36:01Z",
